### CLASS HIERARCHY
extends Microsoft.Agents.AI.AIAgent (base agent framework)

### CONSTRUCTORS

[Constructor 1 - Direct Tool List]
public ChatClientAgent(
  IChatClient chatClient,
  string instructions,
  string name,
  string description,
  IList<AITool> tools,              ← Your tools go here
  ILoggerFactory loggerFactory,
  IServiceProvider services
)

[Constructor 2 - Options-Based]
public ChatClientAgent(
  IChatClient chatClient,
  ChatClientAgentOptions options,   ← Tools in options.AIContextProviders
  ILoggerFactory loggerFactory,
  IServiceProvider services
)

### PROPERTIES

IChatClient ChatClient { get; }
  The underlying chat client (e.g., OpenAI ChatClient, Azure ChatClient)
  Provides model access and tool invocation

ChatHistoryProvider ChatHistoryProvider { get; set; }
  Persists conversation history
  Can be null (in-memory only) or custom implementation

IReadOnlyList<AIContextProvider> AIContextProviders { get; }
  Read-only view of all registered context providers
  These supply tools, skills, and enrichment to the agent

string Name { get; }
  Display name of the agent

string Description { get; }
  Purpose description (sent to LLM)

string Instructions { get; }
  System instructions for the agent

### METHODS

─── Session Lifecycle ───────────────────────────────────────────

public ValueTask<AgentSession> CreateSessionAsync(
  string conversationId,
  CancellationToken cancellationToken
)
  Creates a new conversation session
  Returns: AgentSession for use with Run methods
  Parameters:
    - conversationId: Unique ID for this conversation thread
    - cancellationToken: For async cancellation

public object GetService(Type serviceType, object serviceKey)
  Retrieve services from the dependency container
  Used for middleware composition

─── Synchronous Execution (returns Task<ChatMessage[]>) ───────────

Supports 4 input patterns:
  1. No explicit input (uses existing history)
  2. String message
  3. ChatMessage object
  4. IEnumerable<ChatMessage> (full history)

[Pattern: Run(session, options)]
public Task<ChatMessage[]> RunAsync(
  AgentSession session,
  ChatClientAgentRunOptions options,
  CancellationToken cancellationToken
)
  Executes agent on existing session history

[Pattern: Run(message, session, options)]
public Task<ChatMessage[]> RunAsync(
  string message,                           ← User message
  AgentSession session,
  ChatClientAgentRunOptions options,
  CancellationToken cancellationToken
)
  Adds message to session, executes agent

public Task<ChatMessage[]> RunAsync(
  ChatMessage message,                      ← Structured message
  AgentSession session,
  ChatClientAgentRunOptions options,
  CancellationToken cancellationToken
)

[Pattern: Run(messages, session, options)]
public Task<ChatMessage[]> RunAsync(
  IEnumerable<ChatMessage> messages,        ← Full message list
  AgentSession session,
  ChatClientAgentRunOptions options,
  CancellationToken cancellationToken
)

─── Streaming Execution (returns IAsyncEnumerable<ChatMessage>) ───

Same 4 input patterns as above:

public IAsyncEnumerable<ChatMessage> RunStreamingAsync(
  AgentSession session,
  ChatClientAgentRunOptions options,
  CancellationToken cancellationToken
)

public IAsyncEnumerable<ChatMessage> RunStreamingAsync(
  string message,
  AgentSession session,
  ChatClientAgentRunOptions options,
  CancellationToken cancellationToken
)

public IAsyncEnumerable<ChatMessage> RunStreamingAsync(
  ChatMessage message,
  AgentSession session,
  ChatClientAgentRunOptions options,
  CancellationToken cancellationToken
)

public IAsyncEnumerable<ChatMessage> RunStreamingAsync(
  IEnumerable<ChatMessage> messages,
  AgentSession session,
  ChatClientAgentRunOptions options,
  CancellationToken cancellationToken
)

Usage: 
  await foreach (var msg in agent.RunStreamingAsync("Hello", session, opts, cts)) {
